description: In base 2, neither a palindrome nor becomes a palindrome if trailing 0's are omitted.
comments: These could be called "asymmetric bit strings".Fixed pairs of A057889, complement of A057890
links: Reinhard Zumkeller, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
example: 11 is included because 1011 is asymmetrical, but 12 is not because 001100 is a palindrome.
prog: (Haskell)a057891 n = a057891_list !! (n-1)a057891_list = filter ((== 0) . a178225 . a000265) [1..]-- _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Oct 21 2011
crossrefs: Cf. A061917, A006995. Complement of A057890.
